Insights:
Are there any concrete results you can show at this point? 
To verify the claim that Mamba handles long context efficiently, we conducted two types of experiments. First, we measured inference time using synthetic prompts of increasing length 
(512 to 8192 tokens), which allowed us to isolate computational scaling behavior. Second, we evaluated model performance on a real-world dataset (PubMedQA), where input sequences were 
constructed from question-answer pairs and tokenized into fixed-length blocks. This combination allowed us to assess both efficiency and predictive performance under long-context 
conditions. The results are organized into a table comparing inference time across different context lengths for both models. If Mamba’s runtime increases more slowly than the 
Transformer as the input grows, this provides evidence supporting the claim that Mamba scales more efficiently with long sequences.

